t":"https://sivers.org/nowff","line":33},{"title":"Orbit","target":"https://notes.andymatuschak.org/zDRdgSZguFsSj49gtbf1dJg","line":35},{"title":"Mnemonic medium","target":"https://notes.andymatuschak.org/zKPv6qkSErdRGqyryvgS2wS","line":35},{"title":"Evergreen note-writing as fundamental unit of knowledge work","target":"https://notes.andymatuschak.org/zR6RRbCfY5rFkiimFnaJZKB","line":36},{"title":"The mnemonic medium can be extended to one’s personal notes","target":"https://notes.andymatuschak.org/zWWh96dE6YZYmDCoo37977X","line":37},{"title":"Enacted experiences have incredible potential as a mass medium","target":"https://notes.andymatuschak.org/z984ZZLbG4wREM6HAZAovMB","line":38},{"title":"§Enabling environments, games, and the Primer","target":"https://notes.andymatuschak.org/zGSGS1UHDogPKtvZB5hdT2A","line":38},{"title":"Spaced everything","target":"https://notes.andymatuschak.org/z9hscgkG2TeqgUtu3vAEW3U","line":39},{"title":"Programmable attention","target":"https://notes.andymatuschak.org/zPpaHZYKuBPyoDtgcsiZ9RV","line":39},{"title":"Timeful text","target":"https://notes.andymatuschak.org/zAb9R6nYuTyN6PBC4rQY9aY","line":40},{"title":"Athletes and musicians pursue virtuosity in fundamental skills much more rigorously than knowledge workers do","target":"https://notes.andymatuschak.org/zMX9Lfuz8sGfDUivWZcyWT","line":42},{"title":"Knowledge work rarely involves deliberate practice","target":"https://notes.andymatuschak.org/zMbCwoVdjsqPNyTRRr3phPN","line":43},{"title":"§Taking knowledge work seriously (Stripe convergence talk, 2019-12-12)","target":"https://notes.andymatuschak.org/zBmSSpM1WfFDehxNCBcqSZp","line":44},{"title":"How might we situate tools for thought within intrinsically meaningful contexts?","target":"https://notes.andymatuschak.org/zGD1FxbDZd7WnH7NrhRaVyC","line":45},{"title":"Note-writing practices are generally ineffective","target":"https://notes.andymatuschak.org/zDfV5GX8kKScLkE8Dq1rFUk","line":51},{"title":"People seem to forget most of what t